ProMED-mail
promed@promedmail.org



[The concerns of the Japanese authorities remind those of their
counterparts in the Republic of Ireland during the recent FMD outbreak in
the UK which was identified on 21 Feb 2001. On 28 Feb 2001, following the
information on a suspected FMD case in neighbouring Northern Ireland, the
Irish Minister of Agriculture, Mr Joe Walsh TD, published an "immediate
call to all sporting bodies to postpone events or where this is not
possible to ensure that protective measures are in place so that vehicles
and spectators undergo disinfection." Consequently, the Gaelic Athletic
Association (GAA) decided to postpone games over next week-end. Minister
Walsh expressed his appreciation of the decision. - Mod. AS]
